whereas.text:
Whereas congenital diaphragmatic hernia occurs when the
			 diaphragm fails to fully form, allowing abdominal organs to migrate into the
			 chest cavity and prevent lung growth;

Whereas babies born with congenital diaphragmatic hernia
			 endure extended hospital stays in intensive care with multiple
			 surgeries;

Whereas patients often outgrow congenital diaphragmatic
			 hernia surgical repair, leading to reherniation and requiring additional
			 surgery;

paragraph.text:
designates April
			 2013 as National Congenital Diaphragmatic Hernia Awareness
			 Month;

subparagraph.text:
disseminate
			 information on the importance of good neonatal care for congenital
			 diaphragmatic hernia patients;
